description:
# Task: Implement Nvidia Story Page

## Objective
Create the actual page at /nvidia-story (or chosen URL) that assembles all the components.

## CRITICAL: File Discipline (per AGENTS.md)
- **Data**: All Nvidia story data goes in lib/content.ts - do NOT create lib/nvidia-story-data.ts
- **Components**: Minimize new files. Prefer ONE nvidia-story.tsx file containing all sub-components as internal components, or at most 2 files.
- **Bar for new files is incredibly high** - resist the urge to create many small files

## Recommended File Structure (Minimal)
```
app/nvidia-story/
  page.tsx              # Main page, imports the single component

components/
  nvidia-story.tsx      # ALL Nvidia story UI in one file (internal sub-components)

lib/content.ts          # Add nvidiaStoryData object here
```

## Data Structure (add to lib/content.ts)
```typescript
export const nvidiaStoryData = {
  headline: "The $600B Drop",
  stats: { marketCapDrop: 600, date: "2024-XX-XX", ... },
  timeline: [ { date: "...", event: "..." }, ... ],
  quotes: [ { author: "Matt Levine", text: "...", source: "..." }, ... ],
  podcasts: [ { title: "Bankless", embedUrl: "..." }, ... ],
  essayLink: "/writing/the_short_case_for_nvda",
};
```

## Component Structure (ONE FILE)
```tsx
// components/nvidia-story.tsx
'use client';

// Internal sub-components (not exported)
function HeroSection({ data }) { ... }
function MarketCapChart({ data }) { ... }
function EventTimeline({ events }) { ... }
function QuoteWall({ quotes }) { ... }
function PodcastSection({ podcasts }) { ... }

// Main exported component
export function NvidiaStory() {
  return (
    <>
      <HeroSection />
      <MarketCapChart />
      <EventTimeline />
      <QuoteWall />
      <PodcastSection />
    </>
  );
}
```

## Page File
```tsx
// app/nvidia-story/page.tsx
import { NvidiaStory } from '@/components/nvidia-story';
import { JsonLd } from '@/components/json-ld';
import { nvidiaStoryData } from '@/lib/content';

export const metadata = { ... };

export default function NvidiaStoryPage() {
  return (
    <>
      <JsonLd data={...} />
      <NvidiaStory />
    </>
  );
}
```

## Dependencies
- Design layout task (azv)
- Market cap chart logic (cd6)
- Event timeline logic (dd6)
- Quote wall logic (9t5) - reuses endorsement card
- Podcast section logic (ch3)

Note: The dependent tasks provide the LOGIC/DESIGN, but implementation consolidates into minimal files.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Page renders at /nvidia-story
- [ ] All data lives in lib/content.ts
- [ ] Maximum 2 new component files (ideally 1)
- [ ] Performance: lazy load podcast embeds
- [ ] Accessible and semantic HTML

## Overview
Structure the demo links data and gather all necessary content (descriptions, screenshots, metadata).

## IMPORTANT: File Location
**Add demos to lib/content.ts** - Per AGENTS.md, all site content MUST live in lib/content.ts. Do NOT create lib/demos.ts or any other separate data file.

## Demos to Include

### 1. Agent Mail Viewer
- URL: https://dicklesworthstone.github.io/cass-memory-system-agent-mailbox-viewer/viewer/
- Category: ai-tools
- Technologies: React, TypeScript, MCP Protocol
- Description: Real-time viewer for multi-agent coordination and messaging
- Screenshot needed

### 2. Beads Viewer
- URL: https://dicklesworthstone.github.io/beads_viewer-pages/
- Category: developer-tools
- Technologies: React, Git integration, Issue tracking
- Description: Visual explorer for the beads distributed issue tracking system
- Screenshot needed

### 3. Phage Explorer
- URL: https://phage-explorer.org/
- Category: education
- Technologies: Next.js, Scientific visualization, Educational
- Description: Interactive educational site exploring bacteriophages and their potential
- Screenshot needed

## Data Structure (add to lib/content.ts)
```typescript
// Add this interface and array to lib/content.ts alongside existing content
export interface LiveDemo {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  url: string;
  description: string;
  longDescription?: string;
  previewImage: string;
  technologies: string[];
  category: 'ai-tools' | 'education' | 'developer-tools';
  featured: boolean;
  githubUrl?: string;
}

export const liveDemos: LiveDemo[] = [
  // Add demos here
];
```

## Alternative: Extend Existing Projects
Consider adding these as projects in the existing `projects` array with `kind: 'demo'` rather than creating a separate demos array. This provides consistency with existing patterns.

## Content Tasks
- [ ] Write compelling descriptions for each
- [ ] Capture high-quality screenshots
- [ ] List relevant technologies

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All three demos documented
- [ ] Screenshots captured and optimized  
- [ ] Data added to lib/content.ts (NOT a new file)
- [ ] Descriptions are compelling

## Overview
Gather, curate, and structure all endorsement/testimonial content into a typed data structure.

## IMPORTANT: File Location
**Add endorsements to lib/content.ts** - Per AGENTS.md, all site content MUST live in lib/content.ts. Do NOT create lib/endorsements.ts or any other separate data file.

## Data Sources to Mine
1. **LinkedIn Recommendations**: Extract key quotes from profile
2. **Twitter/X Mentions**: Notable positive mentions, especially around Nvidia incident
3. **Podcast Quotes**: Notable things hosts said about Jeffrey
4. **Email Testimonials**: With permission, any notable client feedback
5. **Public Comments**: HackerNews, Reddit, etc. positive mentions

## Data Structure (add to lib/content.ts)
```typescript
// Add this interface and array to lib/content.ts alongside existing content
export interface Endorsement {
  id: string;
  quote: string;
  author: {
    name: string;
    title?: string;
    company?: string;
    avatar?: string;
  };
  source: {
    type: 'linkedin' | 'twitter' | 'podcast' | 'email' | 'other';
    url?: string;
    platform?: string;
  };
  date?: string;
  tags: string[]; // e.g., ['nvidia', 'technical', 'leadership']
  featured: boolean;
  context?: string;
}

export const endorsements: Endorsement[] = [
  // Add curated endorsements here
];
```

## Curation Guidelines
- Only include genuinely positive, substantive quotes
- Prefer specific praise over generic
- Include diverse sources (not just LinkedIn)
- Prioritize credible/notable endorsers

## Privacy Considerations
- Obtain permission for non-public quotes
- Use initials/anonymous for sensitive sources
- Link to original source where possible

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Minimum 10 quality endorsements curated
- [ ] Data structure added to lib/content.ts (NOT a new file)
- [ ] Tags applied for filtering
- [ ] Featured items marked
